article.description: Lindauer scores 19; High Point beats DIII Ferrum 106-48
article.headline: Lindauer scores 19; High Point beats DIII Ferrum 106-48
article.linkText: Lindauer scores 19; High Point beats DIII Ferrum 106-48
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- Anthony Lindauer scored 19 points to lead High Point to a 106-48 victory over Division III Ferrum on Wednesday. It's the seventh-most points in High Point's men's basketball history and its second 100-point game of the season. K.J. James scored 13 for High Point (7-3), Devante Wallace and Adam Weary had 12 apiece, and Quincy Drye added 10. High Point made 70.9 percent of its shots (39 of 55), including 7 of 10 from 3-point range, and hit 21 of 27 free throws. Lindauer was 5 of 6 from the field, including 3 of 3 from beyond the arc, and hit all six of his free throw attempts. Jamal Pullen scored 14 points and Rashawn Speas had 12 for Ferrum. The Panthers made just 35.6 percent of their shots (16 of 45), including 2 of 12 3-pointers. Ferrum committed 22 turnovers, 16 from steals.
